======================================================================
CONNECTION 1: FIBONACCI ANYONS & JONES POLYNOMIAL
======================================================================

The Fibonacci anyon model is the simplest non-abelian topological
quantum computer. Its fusion rules: П„вЉ—П„ = 1вЉ•П„, giving F-matrices
with entries involving П†. The Jones polynomial at q=e^{2ПЂi/5}
detects Fibonacci anyons.

KEY INSIGHT: Our transfer matrix T_B = [[3,-1],[1,0]] has
eigenvalues П†ВІ and П†^{-2} = П€ВІ. The SAME golden ratio!

Fibonacci anyon F-matrix (basis change for fusion):
  F = [[П†вЃ»В№, П†^(-1/2)], [П†^(-1/2), -П†вЃ»В№]]
    = [[0.618034, 0.786151],
       [0.786151, -0.618034]]

Fibonacci anyon R-matrix (braiding): e^{4ПЂi/5} = -0.809017+0.587785j
  |R| = 1, arg = 4ПЂ/5 = 0.8000 of full turn

Dimension ratios:
  d(П„)/d(1) = П† = 1.618034 (quantum dimension of П„)
  log_П†(F_p) / (p-1) for Interval tournament:
    p= 5: F_p=           5, log_П†(F_p)/(p-1) = 0.836138
    p= 7: F_p=          13, log_П†(F_p)/(p-1) = 0.888365
    p=11: F_p=          89, log_П†(F_p)/(p-1) = 0.932778
    p=13: F_p=         233, log_П†(F_p)/(p-1) = 0.943978
    p=17: F_p=        1597, log_П†(F_p)/(p-1) = 0.957983
    p=19: F_p=        4181, log_П†(F_p)/(p-1) = 0.962651

  OBSERVATION: log_П†(F_p)/(p-1) в†’ 1 as pв†’в€ћ
  This means F_p в‰€ П†^{p-1} asymptotically, which is the Fibonacci
  growth rate. But this is ALSO the total quantum dimension of a
  system of (p-1)/2 Fibonacci anyons!

Jones polynomial connection:
  The Jones polynomial V_K(t) at t = e^{2ПЂi/5} computes the
  amplitude for a braid to return to initial anyon configuration.
  For tournament T on Z_p with connection set S:
  - Each edge (iв†’j) in the tournament = a crossing in a braid
  - The Hamiltonian path count H(T) = 'volume' of the braid closure

Transfer matrix eigenvalues: 2.618034, 0.381966
  = П†ВІ = 2.618034, П€ВІ = 0.381966

Pentagon equation for Fibonacci anyons: (FвЉ—1)(1вЉ—F)(FвЉ—1) = (1вЉ—F)(FвЉ—1)
This coherence condition involves П† in EXACTLY the same way as
our Cassini identity B_{m-1}В·B_{m+1} - B_mВІ = -1 (= Norm in Q(в€љ5))

TOURNAMENT BRAIDING INTERPRETATION:
  Consider p particles on Z_p. Connection set S determines which
  swaps are 'over' vs 'under'. A Hamiltonian path = a maximal braid.
  H(T) = number of inequivalent maximal braids.
  Fibonacci structure в†’ the braid group element lives in the image
  of the Jones representation at q = П†^{-2}.

