CONNECTION 6: TROPICAL CONSTANT Оє IDENTIFICATION
======================================================================

Recall Оє_trop = log(F_p)/log(F_p^{trop}) where F_p^{trop} = max Q_k.
We had Оє в†’ 0.670. Now that Q_1/mВІ в†’ 4/ПЂВІ, let's see:

F_p в‰€ П†^{p-1}, so log F_p в‰€ (p-1)log(П†) в‰€ 2mВ·log(П†)
F_p^{trop} = max Q_k = Q_1 в‰€ 4mВІ/ПЂВІ
log Q_1 в‰€ 2 log m + log(4/ПЂВІ)

Оє = 2mВ·log(П†) / (2 log m + const)
This DIVERGES as mв†’в€ћ! So Оє is NOT a constant.
Let me recheck the definition...

Re-examining: Оє_trop was defined as F_trop / log(F_p)
where F_trop = log(max term in в€Џ(1+Q_k))
The max term is the full product в€ЏQ_k = 1 (PROVED!)
So the max term in the expansion of в€Џ(1+Q_k) is в€ЏQ_kВ·1 if all Q_k > 1,
but actually we need max over all subsets J of в€Џ_{kв€€J} Q_k.

