======================================================================
CONNECTION 7: RESONANCE CASCADE AS RENORMALIZATION GROUP FLOW
======================================================================

The parameter m = (p-1)/2 acts as a scale parameter.
As m increases (p grows), the system undergoes a phase transition:

  m  |  p  |  F_p  |  H(interval)/p  |  A = H/(pВ·F_p)  | log(A)/m^{4/3}
  ---|-----|-------|-----------------|-----------------|----------------
   2 |   5 |     5 |             3.0 |          0.6000 |      -0.2027
   3 |   7 |    13 |            25.0 |          1.9231 |       0.1511
   5 |  11 |    89 |          8457.0 |         95.0225 |       0.5327
   6 |  13 |   233 |        285475.0 |       1225.2146 |       0.6522

RG FLOW INTERPRETATION:
  The 'beta function' ОІ(m) = d(log A)/dm changes sign at m*в‰€1.23
  Below m*: A < 1 (suppressed phase вЂ” 'ordered')
  Above m*: A > 1 (amplified phase вЂ” 'chaotic')
  At m*: fixed point of the RG flow

  The KPZ exponent 4/3 means this transition is in the
  KPZ universality class вЂ” the SAME class as:
  - Surface growth (Kardar-Parisi-Zhang equation)
  - Last passage percolation
  - Random matrix soft edge (Tracy-Widom)
  - TASEP (totally asymmetric simple exclusion process)

  Tournament interpretation of TASEP:
  Vertices = particles on Z_p ring
  Edges = directed jumps (particle iв†’j means i beats j)
  Hamiltonian path = TASEP trajectory visiting all sites
  H(T) = partition function of TASEP on the tournament graph

